<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="378" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Biology:</emphasis>
The species is polyphagous, and is considered an important agricultural pest of innumerable plant species of commercial interest (
<bibRefCitation box="[505,719,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" refId="ref11261" refString="Savage, J., Fortier, A. M., Fournier, F. &amp; Bellavance, V. (2016) Identification of Delia pest species (Diptera: Anthomyiidae) in cultivated crucifers and other vegetable crops in Canada. Canadian Journal of Arthropod Identification, 29, 1 - 40." type="journal article">
Savage 
<emphasis box="[595,651,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="378" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Comments:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[346,511,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" refId="ref10588" refString="Hennig, W. (1955) Los Insectos de Las Islas Juan Fernandez. Revista Chilena de Entomologia, 4, 21 - 34." type="journal article">Hennig (1955)</bibRefCitation>
identified 28 specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bigot, 1885) in Robinson Crusoe" authorityName="(Bigot, 1885) in Robinson Crusoe" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="platura" subSpecies="sanctijacobi">
<emphasis box="[830,1129,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Delia platura sanctijacobi</emphasis>
(Bigot, 1885) in Robinson Crusoe
</taxonomicName>
Island, two in Santa Clara Island and one in Alejandro Selkirk Island (
<tableCitation box="[1033,1118,404,429]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,239,404,427]" captionText="TABLE 1. Anthomyiidae, Fanniidae and Muscidae species recorded from the Juan Fernández Archipelago, with data retrieved from Hennig (1955, 1957), Domínguez (2007) and the present paper. Abbreviatures: RC= Robinson Crusoe Island, AS= Alejandro Selkirk Island, SC= Santa Clara Island; H1 = Hennig (1955); H2 = Hennig (1957); D= Domínguez (2007); P= present paper." pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Table 1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bigot, 1885)" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanctijacobi">
<emphasis box="[1143,1350,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Delia sanctijacobi</emphasis>
(Bigot, 1885)
</taxonomicName>
is now considered a valid species (
<bibRefCitation box="[623,907,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" refId="ref10951" refString="Pape, T. &amp; Thompson, F. C. (2013) Systema Dipterorum. Version 1.5. Family Tables. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / FamilyTables. php (accessed 10 July 2016)" type="journal article">Pape &amp; Thompson 2013</bibRefCitation>
), also with economic importance in Argentina (
<bibRefCitation box="[158,428,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" refId="ref10537" refString="Hamity, M. G. A. &amp; Roman, L. E. N. (1987) Anthomyiidae de interes Agricola en distintos cultivos de altura de Jujuy. Aparicon estacional y mayor abundancia. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 44, 411 - 418." type="journal article">Hamity &amp; Roman 1987</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
